<div xmlns:java="http://xml.apache.org/xslt/java" id="centre_col"><!-- begin original content --><h1>ESSUM37100 - Approval of schemes:
Introduction</h1>
<br>
<p>This section explains the layout of the guidance notes on
approved SAYE share option schemes and gives a brief explanation of
the main requirements for approval. These schemes are also known as
Savings Related Share option schemes. They are referred to in the
legislation as Approved SAYE Option Schemes.
<br>
<br> The legislation relating to approved SAYE share option
schemes was introduced by Finance Act 1980 and is now consolidated
in Schedule 3 Income Tax (Earnings and Pensions) Act 2003. Under
these schemes employees and directors are granted share options
which give them rights to acquire shares. If certain conditions are
satisfied no liability to income tax arises when the options are
exercised. Unlike CSOP schemes, they must be open to all employees.
<br>
<br> The relevant requirements for approval of SAYE share option
schemes are contained within Schedule 3 of ITEPA 2003 and are
concerned with:</p>
<br>
<ul>
<li class="filledcircle">providing participants with legally
enforceable rights to acquire shares, with all features of the
scheme essential or reasonably incidental to that purpose
(paragraph 5)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">the nature of the shares over which
options can be granted (paragraphs 17 - 22)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">the requirement for a linked savings
arrangement (paragraphs 23 &ndash; 26)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">the possible facility to exchange options
on a takeover (paragraphs 38 and 39)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">who can participate in the scheme
(paragraphs 9 - 16)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">setting limits on contributions by each
participant (paragraph 25)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">the price at which options can be
exercised (paragraph 28)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">circumstances where participants must be
able to exercise their options (paragraphs 30 &ndash; 34)</li>
</ul>
<h2>Statutory provisions and requirements</h2>
<p>The statutory provisions and requirements relate to:</p>
<br>
